# Data Deletion Request for SeenMatch: Last Seen Alert

Effective date: May 10, 2026

SeenMatch: Last Seen Alert does not create its own user account system. The app uses Telegram sign-in only to access visible online / last-seen status information available to the signed-in Telegram account.

## How to request data deletion

If you want to request deletion of data related to your use of SeenMatch, please contact us by email:

icebreakerstudios.app@outlook.com

Use the subject line:

Data Deletion Request - SeenMatch

In your email, please include:

- The phone number used for Telegram sign-in, if applicable
- A short statement saying that you want your SeenMatch-related data deleted

We will review and process deletion requests within a reasonable time.

## What data can be deleted

Depending on your app usage, deletion may include:

- Selected contact identifiers stored by the app
- Local activity logs generated by the app
- Visible online / last-seen activity records stored by the app
- App-related diagnostic records that can reasonably be associated with your request

## Local device data

Most SeenMatch activity data is stored locally on your device.

You can also delete local app data at any time by:

1. Opening your device Settings
2. Going to Apps
3. Selecting SeenMatch
4. Choosing Storage
5. Tapping Clear data

You can also uninstall the app to remove local app data from your device.

## Data we do not control

SeenMatch does not control your Telegram account or Telegram data. To delete your Telegram account or Telegram data, you must use Telegram’s own account and privacy tools.

If Premium subscriptions are enabled, payment and subscription records may be handled by Google Play and RevenueCat. Some records may be retained where required for billing, fraud prevention, tax, legal, or security reasons.

